| ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| Connectivity Loss               | Delayed monitoring or control actions   |
| Sensor Failure                  | Incorrect operational decisions         |
| Actuator Failure                | Inability to execute corrective actions |
| Unauthorized Access             | Security and operational risks          |
| Dependence on External Services | Reduced functionality during outages    |
| Unplanned Growth                | Performance degradation                 |

---

## 11. Risk Mitigation

* Use secure communication mechanisms.
* Maintain local functionality when cloud services are unavailable.
* Validate sensor data before critical actions.
* Define safe states for actuators.
* Perform regular system testing.
* Monitor network health and device status.
* Use open standards to reduce technological lock-in.

---

## 12. Conclusions

The SoilSense platform demonstrates how IoT technologies can generate tangible business value through continuous monitoring, remote control, historical data management, and operational visibility.

The architecture provides a scalable and interoperable foundation based on ESP32-C6 devices, OpenThread networking, Matter integration, MQTT communication, and dashboard-based user interaction.

From a business perspective, SoilSense improves operational efficiency, supports informed decision-making, reduces manual effort, and establishes a flexible platform capable of evolving with future requirements.
